NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD, Petitioner, v. Leroy C. PHENIX, Doing Business as the L. C. Phenix Company, Respondent. No. 9043. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 12, 1938. Charles Fahy, Gen. Counsel, National Labor Relations Board, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Ben C. Cohen, of Los Angeles, Cal., for respondent.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered petition to enforce granted, and that a judgment be entered in the minutes of this court enforcing the Order of the National Labor Relations Board herein.
